main event: A bluish-white object similar to a shining star was observed making two turns and a circle at Kadena AFB, Okinawa.
interesting points: The object was approximately 50 feet in wing span and silver in color, shaped like two saucers back-to-back.
The object was observed proceeding in a zigzag motion, making another complete circle, and disappearing to the southeast.
The object was first sighted above in level flight, making a sharp zigzag motion, and then taking another complete circle before disappearing.
The object was observed for a duration of 37 minutes, from 21:15 on December 23, 1953, to 22:10 on December 25, 1954.
The object was detected on radar, with the first sighting at 23,500 feet and then coming down to 2,250 feet.
sighted object: bluish-white object similar to a shining star
